SETUP INSTRUCTIONS FOR AI SHOPPING ASSISTANT
Step 1: Install Python
Download and install Python (version 3.10 or above) from the official website:
https://www.python.org/downloads/
Make sure to check the box:
[✓] Add Python to PATH
Step 2: Create a Virtual Environment
Open a terminal or command prompt and navigate to the Shopping Assistant project folder, then run:
For Windows:
python -m venv venv
venv\Scripts\activate
For macOS/Linux:
python3 -m venv venv
source venv/bin/activate
Step 3: Upgrade pip (recommended)
pip install --upgrade pip
Step 4: Install Required Dependencies
This project does not require any external libraries. It only uses Python’s built-in features.
Step 5: Run the AI Shopping Assistant Program
After activating the virtual environment, run the program:
python shopping_assistant.py
